\

\fs52 Salad:\
1 1/2 cups dry soybeans, soaked\
1 1/2 cups dry red wheat berries, soaked\
6 scallions, finely chopped\
2 medium carrots, finely chopped\
2 small cucumbers, seeded & finely chopped\
1/2 red bell pepper, finely chopped\
1 cup cottage cheese\
1 cup minced flat-leaf parsley\
1/2 cup minced fresh dill\
\
Dressing:\
1/2 cup cider vinegar\
2 teaspoons kosher salt\
Freshly ground black pepper, to taste\
1/2 cup mayonnaise\
3-4 cloves of garlic, minced\
\
Place the beans in separate pots & cover by a few inches of water. Soak the beans for 4 hours, or overnight.\
Drain the beans, place them back in their pots & fill with fresh water. Bring both pots to a boil, partially cover & simmer until tender.\
The wheat berries will take about 45 minutes. The soybeans will take about 1 hour 15 minutes.\
The beans should be cooked to a crunchy/chewy, yet tender texture. Do not overcook.\
When cooked, drain the beans in a colander. Place them in a large mixing bowl.\
Combine with all the other salad ingredients.\
Mix the dressing ingredients, add them to the bowl & mix well.\
